  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to investigate the change in iron metabolism in relation to malaria
      and helminth infections using a stable isotope technique.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to determine how iron metabolism in subjects with infectious diseases
      (malaria, hookworm or S. haematobium) differs while infected and after treatment, i.e. the
      same individuals will be restudied while free of infection.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
